Prisoner Strong. Was not that brother in the room? - No;
Bob Pearson
was in the room.

Were there any more that you do not know their names? - No;
Thomas Gray
, the prisoner, is the person I mean.

I am one of the City Marshal's men; I went to Fonseca's house with Mr. Miller and found a large quantity of of halfpence; I cannot say the day; I saw Mr. Fonseca at first entrance, in a little part of the house, then, in another part I found Mrs. Cole; he absconded immediately; I found a large quantity of halfpence, they are here;
Mary Cole
was tried here last session.
